newsitem.title: TAIWAN: Taiwan interbank rate ends lower, uptrend seen.
newsitem.headline: Taiwan interbank rate ends lower, uptrend seen.

text.p: Taiwan's interbank rate closed slightly lower on Wednesday, but dealers said payments for T$30 billion in government bonds, which were auctioned on Tuesday, were seen tightening liquidity.
The overnight interbank rate finished at 5.426 percent against Tuesday's 5.428 close, with 30-day commercial paper at 5.40-5.45 against 5.40-5.50.
The central bank injected T$6.53 billion in funds on Wednesday to maintain stable liquidity in the banking system.
The 10-year 84/1 government bond yield was at 5.820 and the 10-year construction bond yield at 5.9675.-- Julie Hu (5080815)
